\chapter{I/O Capture}
\label{capture}

When a student runs their program, we want to record everything they see
and type---standard output, standard error, and standard input---in the
order it actually happens.
The key design choice is a single shared buffer rather than three separate
ones: if the program prints a prompt to stdout, the student types a
response on stdin, and then the program prints output, we need to
preserve that interleaving to make the log readable.

\section{Code overview}

The module provides three classes: [[IOLog]] as the shared buffer, and
[[StreamCapture]] and [[InputCapture]] as transparent wrappers around
the standard streams.

